<paragraph id="8BD436C2871FAA0046A0FB16DE16AFB5" blockId="4.[189,1399,1252,1425]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
This species was described based on a single female specimen collected by the English traveler, naturalist, ornithologist and entomologist William Frederick Henry Rosenberg (
<date id="FFD51002871FAA00427BFAFBDF8CAF01" box="[1126,1260,1289,1316]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1868" valueMax="1957">1868–1957</date>
) who made collecting trips to northern South America (Günter 1912). The 
<typeStatus id="54D08860871FAA00458AFADFD89EAF62" box="[919,1022,1325,1351]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="13502A47871FAA004210FADFDF30AF62" box="[1037,1104,1325,1351]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1469,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1398,1469,1924]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Centris lilacina Cockerell, 1919, holotype, ♀ (NMNH; USNM ENT 00534201). A. Frontal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3722952" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3722952/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) is housed at the 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE07871FAA004300FADCDE17AF6D" box="[1309,1399,1326,1352]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
under the number 21656 and has the following data label: Palcazu 
<collectingCountry id="F37C7652871FAA0045DDFAA0D896AF49" box="[960,1014,1362,1388]" name="Peru" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Peru</collectingCountry>
[printed]\ Collection Rosenberg\ 
